Subject:
Rotaract Club: Oral Health Care

Body:
Dear all,
Rotaract club of IIT Madras is proud to announce it's first event for this
academic year. We will be having an inspiring speaker sessions followed up
by Dental Health Camp. Schedule is as follows:

3:00 pm to 3:30 pm : How Rotary can help you become a global citizen. Rtn
P.E. Ramakrishnan would be enlightening us about the role of Rotary around
the globe and how it helps us to become a global citizen. Mr. Ram is an
successful Entrepreneur and Past President of Rotary club of Madras East.
He has held several positions within Rotary organization and is a great
Ambassador of Rotary Organization.

3:35 pm to 4:00 pm: Oral Health Care session by Dr Sandhya.
This session will include 25 minutes of health talk where three major
domains will be covered, which are 
1) Oral care for daily maintenance of Oral Health
2) Commonest dental problems at adolescence and it's prevention
3) How stress and Oral health are related

4:00 pm to 7:00 pm: Free Dental Checkup for 100+ students. Students will
be selected on first come first serve basis.

Venue for this is CRC, room no. 301. Be there on time if you don't want to
miss your free pass.
 

Warm Regards,
